sql:
WITH attendance_count AS (
  SELECT 
    Conference_ID, 
    COUNT(DISTINCT staff_ID) AS attendants
  FROM conference_participation
  GROUP BY Conference_ID
),
ranked_conferences AS (
  SELECT 
    Conference_ID, 
    attendants,
    DENSE_RANK() OVER (ORDER BY attendants DESC) AS rnk
  FROM attendance_count
)
SELECT c.Conference_Name
FROM conference c
JOIN ranked_conferences rc ON c.Conference_ID = rc.Conference_ID
WHERE rc.rnk <= 2;
question: Find the name of the conferences that have the top 2 most number of attendants.

sql:
WITH attendance_counts AS (
  SELECT Conference_ID, COUNT(DISTINCT staff_ID) AS attendant_count
  FROM conference_participation
  GROUP BY Conference_ID
), ranked_conferences AS (
  SELECT Conference_ID, attendant_count,
         DENSE_RANK() OVER (ORDER BY attendant_count DESC) AS rank
  FROM attendance_counts
)
SELECT c.Conference_Name
FROM ranked_conferences rc
JOIN conference c ON rc.Conference_ID = c.Conference_ID
WHERE rc.rank <= 2;

sql:
WITH attendance_counts AS (
  SELECT 
    Conference_ID, 
    COUNT(DISTINCT staff_ID) AS attendant_count
  FROM conference_participation
  GROUP BY Conference_ID
),
top2_counts AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT attendant_count
  FROM attendance_counts
  ORDER BY attendant_count DESC
  LIMIT 2
)
SELECT c.Conference_Name
FROM conference c
JOIN attendance_counts ac ON c.Conference_ID = ac.Conference_ID
WHERE ac.attendant_count IN (SELECT attendant_count FROM top2_counts)
ORDER BY ac.attendant_count DESC, c.Conference_Name;
question: Find the name of the conferences that have the top 2 most number of attendants.

  SELECT 
    Conference_ID, 
    COUNT(staff_ID) AS attendants_count
  FROM conference_participation

),
top2 AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT attendants_count
  FROM attendance_counts

  LIMIT 2
)
SELECT c.Conference_Name
FROM conference c
JOIN attendance_counts ac ON c.Conference_ID = ac.Conference_ID
WHERE ac.attendants_count IN (SELECT attendants_count FROM top2)
ORDER BY ac.attendants_count DESC, c.Conference_Name;
